Others praised Extra Place as a rarity – a city fragment almost for nothing changed that should be left alone.
Jeremiah Moss, who has a blog called Jeremiah's Vanishing New York (subtitled, "The Book of Complaints: A Little Nostalgic Look at the City Going Down"), published part of a City History Speech that appeared on The New Yorker in 1952.
